# Design Guidelines

## App Shell Design Principles

### Use Default Styles
- **Always use shadcn/ui and Tailwind defaults** for the app shell (navigation, sidebars, layout, components)
- **Don't override** shadcn component styles unless absolutely necessary
- Trust the defaults - they're well-designed and accessible

### Aesthetic
- **Minimalist** - Remove unnecessary visual elements. Lean towards no color
- **Clean** - Simple, clear hierarchy
- **Lots of whitespace** - Generous spacing, breathing room
- **Modern** - Contemporary, professional look

---

## App Shell vs VCA Components

### App Shell (Navigation, Sidebars, Layout)
Use standard Tailwind and shadcn/ui:
```tsx
// Good - standard Tailwind colors
<div className="bg-white text-gray-900 border-gray-200">

// Good - default shadcn components
<Tabs>
  <TabsList>
    <TabsTrigger>Tab Name</TabsTrigger>
  </TabsList>
</Tabs>
```

### VCA Components (Chat Bubbles, Messages)
Use VCA design tokens with `vca-` prefix:
```tsx
// Good - VCA-specific styling
<div className="bg-vca-background text-vca-text border-vca-border">
```

